docs/pilot-features/pilot-core.json:7:      "shortSummary": "Guides a pilot user through account setup, schedule, Telegram connection, portfolio entry, and then shows the portfolio health overview.",
docs/pilot-features/pilot-core.json:8:      "detailedExplanation": "The onboarding flow collects user credentials or password change input, daily/weekly schedule preferences, optional Telegram bot details, portfolio accounts and positions, and optional position guidance before routing the user into the main portfolio screen. The portfolio screen shows a concise health headline, holdings, account grouping, active analysis jobs, attention cards, and quick-check controls derived from current portfolio and verdict data.",
docs/pilot-features/pilot-core.json:20:        "Client-side validation blocks missing account, password, ticker, share, average-price, and Telegram input before submission.",
docs/pilot-features/pilot-core.json:88:      "shortSummary": "Surfaces report, daily brief, market news, and web notification activity in the app and lets users tune notification channels.",
docs/pilot-features/pilot-core.json:89:      "detailedExplanation": "The Alerts page fetches the report feed with alert-focused filters and expandable cards. The app shell polls unread web notifications and turns them into toasts, then marks them read. Settings exposes primary channel, channel enablement, and category preferences for daily briefs, report runs, and market news.",
docs/pilot-features/pilot-core.json:93:        "User opens Settings and saves notification channel/category preferences."
docs/pilot-features/pilot-core.json:97:        "Unavailable external channels are disabled or omitted from channel choices.",
docs/pilot-features/pilot-core.json:103:        "Notification API list and mark-read routes clamp limits and filter channel values to supported channels."
